      <div
        class="c2"
      >
        <h2
          class="c3"
        >
          Hints
        </h2>
        <div
          class="c4"
        >
          <ul
            class="c15"
          >
            <li>
              The code must be a single function that returns a string value to copy.
            </li>
            <li>
              <b>
                *BETA*
              </b>
               Returning
               
              <code>
                {
                "html":"...","text": "..."
                }
              </code>
               
              to copy as rich text & plain text. This interface may change in future.
            </li>
            <li>
              <code>
                render(template, view)
              </code>
               - You can render
               
              <a
                href="https://github.com/janl/mustache.js"
                rel="noreferrer noopener"
                target="_blank"
              >
                mustache
              </a>
               
              templates.
            </li>
            <li>
              <code>
                new DOMParser().parseFromString(content, 'text/html')
              </code>
              - You can use
               
              <a
                href="https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/API/DOMParser"
                rel="noreferrer noopener"
                target="_blank"
              >
                <code>
                  DOMParser
                </code>
              </a>
               
              to query the page document.
            </li>
            <li>
              To feedback an error, use 
              <code>
                throw new Error(...)
              </code>
              . It will appear at the function that produced the error.
            </li>
            <li>
              The code runs safely under the
               
              <a
                href="https://developer.chrome.com/apps/sandboxingEval"
                rel="noreferrer noopener"
                target="_blank"
              >
                sandbox
              </a>
              , not under the page.
            </li>
            <li>
              Visit
               
              <a
                href="https://github.com/pokutuna/chrome-cocopy/blob/master/gallery/README.md"
                rel="noreferrer noopener"
                target="_blank"
              >
                Function Gallery
              </a>
               
              to find new function and see sample codes.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div
        class="c2"
      >
        <h2
